Defending Champ Rangers Tie Hearts 1-1 in Scottish League Opener

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-23T14:08:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-23/defending-champ-rangers-tie-hearts-1-1-in-scottish-league-opener.html
Defending champion Rangers rallied
to tie Hearts 1-1 in the opening game of the season in soccer’s
Scottish Premier League.  Steve Naismith’s header in the 58th minute earned Rangers
the home draw at the Ibrox stadium in Glasgow. David Obura gave
Hearts the lead with a header in the 16th minute.  It was the first game for new Rangers manager Ally McCoist,
who replaced Walter Smith after the club won its record-
extending 54th league title last season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  